<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Handwritten copies in one of the bound volumes used by the team of clerks on GW's headquarters staff who worked from 1781-83 under the direction of Lt. Col. Richard Varick to record correspondence, orders, instructions, and related items from GWs Revolutionary War papers ]">Varick transcript</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
 Only the letter-book copy in the Schuyler Papers includes the full postscript. Part of it appears in the copy in PCC, item 153.</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0096-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0096-fn-0001">1</a>
	
   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0092" class="document">Council of War, this date</a>. For Schuylers letter to Hancock of 13 Jan., see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0056&amp;expandNote=GEWN-03-03-02-0056-fn-0002#GEWN-03-03-02-0056-fn-0002" class="document">Schuyler to GW, that date, n.2</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0096-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0096-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0099" class="document">Circular to the Governments of Massachusetts, Connecticut, and New Hampshire, 19 Jan. 1776</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0096-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0096-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>Gen. David Wooster appealed to Col. Seth Warner on 6 Jan. to send 5, 6 or 700 of his Green Mountain Boys as fast as they are Collected (<span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>), but by early March only 417 had reached Wooster. For the men being raised in Connecticut, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0097" class="document">Jonathan Trumbull, Sr., to GW, this date</a>. For other reinforcements sent to Canada, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0118" class="document">Schuyler to GW, 22 Jan. 1776</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-03-03-02-0096-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-03-03-02-0096-fn-0004">4</a>
	
   <p>Donald Campbells letters to David Wooster of 31 Dec. 1775 and 2 Jan. 1776 were enclosed in <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-03-03-02-0056" class="document">Schuylers letter to GW of 13 January</a>. Lt. Col. Christopher Greene and his men were captured at Quebec.</p>

</div>
